Class IRBallot

java.lang.Object
IRBallot
public class IRBallot
extends java.lang.Object
Creates an IRBallot object. This represents a ballot used in the IR algorithm.

  • Constructor Details

    • IRBallot

      public IRBallot​(java.lang.String ballotString, char[] candidateParties, java.lang.String[] candidateNamesOnly, int id)
      This is the IR ballot Constructor. This method constructs the IR ballot object.
      Parameters:
      ballotString - A string containing the ranking of each candidate on the ballot. All candidates do not have to be ranked.
      candidateParties - a array of characters that contains each candidate's respective party.
      candidateNamesOnly - an array of strings that contains the names of the candidates.
      id - an integer id that uniquely identifies each ballot.

    • setNewTopPick

      public java.lang.Boolean setNewTopPick​(java.util.ArrayList<Candidate> eliminatedCandidates)
      returns true and sets a new top pick candidate if there is one available. Returns false if there is not another candidate available to be selected from the ballot.
      Parameters:
      eliminatedCandidates - is an ArrayList of eliminated candidates.
      Returns:
      returns true if a new top pick candidate has been found for the ballot or if a ballot does not need to be thrown out and returns false otherwise.
